<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A 33-year-old man is fighting for his life after being shot in the stomach with a crossbow in west London last night.</p>

<p>Metropolitan Police officers were called to Pield Heath Road near the junction with Copperfield Avenue in Uxbridge by London Ambulance crews just after 8pm.</p>

<p>They discovered the victim with a serious injury inflicted by the crossbow arrow.</p>

<p>He was rushed to hospital, where he remains in a 'life-threatening' condition. </p>

<p>Scotland Yard has not made any arrests and a cordon remains at the scene.</p>
